modules.description: Provides functions to annotate and record execution traces of Lwt-based programs, capturing events at the thread level. Works with Lwt threads, timestamps, and custom event markers to create structured trace data. Used to debug and visualize asynchronous execution flow in Mirage unikernels or similar systems.

Tracks process execution on Xen by capturing timestamps and managing shared memory buffers. It uses bigendian byte strings and shared memory pages to record and transfer trace data between domains. The module enables low-level process monitoring and inter-domain communication with precise timing.
